The paper discusses a testing theory for software product lines, which falls under the category of software engineering (cs.SE). The use of Modal Interface Automata (MIA) as a behavioral specification formalism suggests that the paper may also be relevant to the sub-category of product line engineering (cs.PL). The paper also discusses refinement and compositionality properties, which are relevant to the sub-categories of logic in computer science (cs.LO) and formal languages and automata theory (cs.FL). Finally, the paper may also be relevant to the sub-category of language and automata theory (cs.LG) due to its use of automata-based formalisms.
